node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. This is a new and dangerous tactic to recruit teens to drive migrants from the US-Mexico border to Houston and other Texas cities — with one video offering $4,500 per person they smuggle. CNN's @rosaflorescnn reports.

node.title: Mexican cartels are recruiting teens on TikTok to smuggle migrants

node.text: Take a look at Tokyo’s Olympic Village, a city within a city where elite athletes from all over the world will spend their time when they’re not competing for Olympic gold. But the pandemic means things look very different to Olympic Villages of the past, as @selinawangtv finds out.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 19, 2021. May be an image of map, outdoors and text that says 'North Road Taliban presence Taliban presence North Gate Military side KABUL INTL. AIRPORT The Taliban control the civilian side of the airport Runway Civilian side Main entrance They also control the road leading to the airport, and the main entrance Taliban checkpoint as observed by the New York Times Airport Road Image; Planet Labs US Embassy CNN'.

node.text: Frantic Afghans looking to escape are struggling to get through Taliban checkpoints and into Kabul's airport. The US embassy in the city warned people on Wednesday evening that it cannot ensure safe passage to the airport. Right now, the Taliban controls the civilian side of the airport, including the road to the airport and the main entrance.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'An Olympian sold her silver medal to help a family pay for their baby's heart surgery CNN'.

node.text:
Polish javelin thrower Maria Andrejczyk auctioned off her Tokyo 2020 Olympic silver medal to fund a life-saving heart surgery for an eight-month-old baby. Żabka, a Polish supermarket chain, won the auction with a bid of $125,000, and then announced that it will be returning the medal to Andrejczyk.⁠
⁠
(📸: Martin Meissner/AP)⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The rate of Covid-19 hospitalizations for children and adults under 50 reach their highest levels yet, CDC data shows CNN'.

node.text: Every age group under 50 has surpassed its previous record of Covid hospitalizations. The biggest increase was in adults ages 30 to 39 and children under 18, both of which were more than 30% higher than their previous peak, according to data from the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A Singapore court sentenced a British man to six weeks in prison for not wearing a face mask Singapore has kept its coronavirus outbreaks under control, in part due to its strict enforcement. CNN'.

node.text: A Singapore court sentenced a British man to six weeks in prison on Wednesday, local media reported, after he repeatedly breached coronavirus protocols by refusing to wear a face mask in public. Singapore is well-known for its enforcement of strict rules and has jailed and fined others for breaking Covid-19 regulations.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Garth Brooks cancels his tour because of the Delta variant: 'I must do my part' C CNN'.

node.text:
Country superstar Garth Brooks is canceling the next five stops on his upcoming shows because of the resurgence of the pandemic. He said he's hopeful that he can find new dates "and start over when this wave seems to be behind us."⁠
⁠
(📸: Drew Angerer/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The Taliban are sitting on $1 trillion worth of minerals the world desperately needs CINN'.

node.text:
The swift fall of Afghanistan to Taliban fighters has triggered a humanitarian crisis, with thousands trying to flee the country. It's also brought renewed focus on Afghanistan's vast untapped mineral wealth, resources that could transform its economic prospects if ever developed.⁠
⁠
Supplies of minerals such as iron, copper and gold are scattered across the country. There are also rare earth minerals and, perhaps most importantly, what could be one of the world's biggest deposits of lithium — an essential but scarce component in rechargeable batteries and other technologies vital to tackling the climate crisis.⁠
⁠
(📸: Matthew C. Rains/Tribune News Service/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, sky and text that says 'This teen pilot hopes to be the youngest woman to fly solo around the world MSZOLO 0ககல CNN'.

node.text:
Zara Rutherford, 19, set off Wednesday on the trip of a lifetime: a 32,000-mile journey around the world. She hopes to set the record for the youngest woman to solo circumnavigate the globe — and inspire more girls and women to pursue careers in science and aviation.

(📸: FlyZolo / Beatrice De Smet)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Are boosters unusual when it comes vaccines? Not at all. Many vaccines require multiple doses to achieve the full immune effect. -The polio vaccine requires four doses. -The hepatitis vaccine requires three doses. There are other vaccines that require occasional "boosts" because immunity may wane over time. -The tetanus-diphtheria vaccine is supposed to be given to adults every 10 years. There are other vaccines that need to be administered even more often. -The influenza vaccine needs to be updated every year because there are new strains every season. CNN VACCINE BOOSTERS'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Does a booster mean that the vaccine isn't working? No. We are still learning about Covid-19 and it may be that a third booster shot is needed to finish the series, and after that, we don't need additional immunity It may also be that immunity diminishes over time and an occasional booster will help increase immunity. According to estimates from US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention data, the Covid-19 vaccines protect us from severe illness by about 25 times. Vaccination also reduces the chance of getting Covid-19 by about eight times. CNN VACCINE BOOSTERS'.

More guidance is expected soon for other groups. For right now, it's best to speak with your doctor. node.text: On the streets outside the Kabul airport, it's extremely chaotic with Taliban fighters all around and a constant stream of gunfire. "One man shouted at me to cover my face or he wouldn't talk to me. He was carrying a huge makeshift whip," said @clarissawardcnn. "This one fighter just lifted his gun up into the air as if he was about to start firing rounds, so we had to run and take cover."
